                  <Abstract ID="Abs1" Language="En">
                     <Heading>Abstract</Heading>
                     <Para>We have developed a new automatic ultrafiltration control system balanced with a blood volume (BV) monitor. This system has an algorithm that automatically controls the ultrafiltration rate (UFR), making a balance with blood volume during hemodialysis (HD). This system has been used in hospitalized chronic HD patients with some complications. The frequency of hypotension events during HD sessions was significantly reduced, demonstrating that this system controls UFR very safely. Furthermore, a personal computer connected with this system records trends in blood pressure, BV, UFR, and other values of the HD console. Records of several HD sessions are filed in a floppy disk. The electronic records are easily referred to monthly by HD staff in the clinic. The real-time data also can be sent to the HD center through a computer network system. This system could be used in patients undergoing home HD.</Para>
                  </Abstract>
